column54: Without qualifying our opinion, we refer to the disclosures in note 3, from which it is evident that the company's going concern is dependent on a cash contribution. The parent company has undertaken to contribute the cash neccessary to PocketMobile ApS to meet its obligations as they fall due in respect of the liabilities taken into account in the accounts of PocketMobile ApS for the financial year 2015. The parent company also confirms its current intention to provide all such further support as may be required for PocketMobile ApS to meet all such further liabilities as it may incur in connection with its ordinary business for the period ending 30 June 2017. Accordingly, the management has presented the financial statements on a going concern basis. We did not find any reason to take a different view in respect.
